  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Brake Master Power Function Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. airtight inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "693_4.0_jpn_11581606_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Start the engine. Warm-up operation until the radiator fan operates twice. Stop the engine. Depress the pedal with normal brake force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "The first pedal stroke should be large (A), and as the pedal is depressed two or three times, the pedal stroke should decrease (B). In case of airtightness failure, inspect the airtightness of the following parts Start the engine again. Pedal with normal tread force. The engine is stopped in that state."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Check valve (built into the vacuum hose)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Check valve (built into the vacuum hose)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Vacuum hoses and pipes"
        },
        {
          "text": "Vacuum hoses and pipes"
        },
        {
          "text": "Master Power"
        },
        {
          "text": "Master Power"
        },
        {
          "text": "O-ring of master cylinder"
        },
        {
          "text": "O-ring of master cylinder"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "693_4.0_jpn_11581607_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "9",
      "text": "Keep the pedal depressed for approximately 30 seconds. If the pedal height does not change, the airtightness is good under load."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "693_4.0_jpn_11581608_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the special tool (vacuum gauge kit) and the appropriate hose (A) between the Master Power and Master Power vacuum hose (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Thread sealing tape should be wrapped around the vacuum gauge threads when connecting the vacuum gauge kit to the tube joint adapter."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Reference Negative Pressure Reduction Degree"
          },
          {
            "text": "2.7 kPa (20 mmHg) or less (for 20 seconds)"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Check valve (built into the vacuum hose)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Check valve (built into the vacuum hose)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Vacuum hoses and pipes"
        },
        {
          "text": "Vacuum hoses and pipes"
        },
        {
          "text": "Master Power"
        },
        {
          "text": "Master Power"
        },
        {
          "text": "O-ring of master cylinder"
        },
        {
          "text": "O-ring of master cylinder"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Functional Tests"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "693_4.0_jpn_11581609_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Attach the special tool to the master cylinder as shown in the figure. Bleed air from the air release valve (B) of the dedicated tool."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The flare pipe of the dedicated tool (A) has different shapes at both ends, so be careful when installing it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "693_4.0_jpn_11581610_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "The brake pedal is pressed with a force gauge (A) at 98 N (10 kgf) and 294 N (30 kgf), and if the standard output hydraulic pressure is generated at each negative pressure, it is good. If the standard output fluid pressure cannot be obtained, check the master power airtightness, and if normal, replace the master cylinder as an assembly."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "negative pressure kPa（mmHg）",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "tread (of a wheel) N（kgf）",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Output hydraulic pressure kPa（kgf/cm 2 ) or more",
            "header": true
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "0（0）"
          },
          {
            "text": "98（10.0）"
          },
          {
            "text": "173kPa（1.76kgf/cm 2 ）"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "294（30.0）"
          },
          {
            "text": "2728kPa（27.82kgf/cm 2 ）"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "66.7（500）"
          },
          {
            "text": "98（10.0）"
          },
          {
            "text": "4764kPa（48.58kgf/cm 2 ）"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "294（30.0）"
          },
          {
            "text": "6297kPa（64.21kgf/cm 2 ）"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Check valve Check valve"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "693_4.0_jpn_11581611_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the vacuum hose (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "The check valve (B) is good if it vents when air is blown in from the master power side and does not vent when air is blown in from the opposite direction. If the check valve is defective, replace the vacuum hose as an assembly."
    }
  ],
